        <div class="block text-block">
         <h3 class="block-header">
          About
          <span>
           UCSC Linguistics
          </span>
         </h3>
         <div class="inner">
          <p>
           The Department of Linguistics at UC Santa Cruz is known for marrying careful, detailed empirical examination of particular languages with rigorous theoretical analysis to advance the understanding of human linguistic ability. The department has strengths in morphology, phonetics, phonology, pragmatics, psycholinguistics, semantics, and syntax, training its students in a range of computational, experimental, and fieldwork methodologies. It offers two
           <a href="undergraduate/programs/index.html">
            undergraduate
           </a>
           majors, in linguistics and language studies, as well as
           <a href="graduate/programs/index.html">
            graduate
           </a>
           programs (MA and PhD) in theoretical and experimental linguistics, preparing students for careers in research, teaching, and industry.
          </p>
          <p>
           <a href="about/index.html" title="About">
            Read more
           </a>
          </p>
         </div>
        </div>
       </div>
